<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1810,2014]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,649]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1810,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Description.</emphasis>
Total length, 
<quantity box="[500,589,1810,1834]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. Wing length, 
<quantity box="[753,843,1810,1834]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="6.4">6.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[854,993,1811,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Male. Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1008,1114,1810,1834]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[200,1365,176,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,145,1247]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Psilochlorops, head, dorsal and lateral view. 1, 7. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 2, 8. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 3, 9. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 4, 10. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 5, 11. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 6, 12. Psilochlorops flavisoma (holotype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214703/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Figs. 3, 9</figureCitation>
). Head dark brown dorsally, light brown ventrally, slightly wider than thorax, rather broader than long in dorsal view, longer than high in lateral view; frontal triangle brown, margins sigmoid, reaching anterior margin of frons; occiput dark, with fine setulae; gena light brown, about 
<number box="[427,476,1918,1942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="0.25">0.25</number>
eye height, postgena about half eye height; eye rounded, long axis diagonal; clypeus brownish, dusted; labella light brown; palpus dark brown. First flagellomere dark yellow, with dark brown area at apex; arista dark brown. One row of interfrontals inside frontal triangle; postocellars divergent; inner and outer verticals not observable; one row of setulae at lower margin of gena, no distinct vibrissa. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1171,1260,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1279,1376,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[197,1394,607,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,574,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Psilochlorops, mesonotum, dorsal view. 13. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 14. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 15. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 16. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 17. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 18. Psilochlorops flavisoma (paratype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214704/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1424,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[167,1409,883,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,845,1691]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 22. Habitus. 23. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 24. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214706/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">22</figureCitation>
). Scutum less than twice as long as broad, brown, with five blackish stripes, with light pilosity; scutellum brownish. Pleura dark yellow, post–pronotum light brown with a blackish mark, no bristles; black markings along ventral margin of anepisternum, and on ventral half of katepisternum and anepimeron. Halter with brown stem, yellow knob. Coxae dark yellow, fore femur and tibia black, mid and hind femora and tibiae dark brown to blackish, tibial organ brownish, tarsi dark yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[545,609,331,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Wing</emphasis>
. Brownish. Costal sections one to four: 
<date box="[1068,1201,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1943-07-30" valueMax="1943-07-20" valueMin="1943-07-30">
<number box="[1068,1098,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="43.0">43</number>
- 
<number box="[1106,1136,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="30.0">30</number>
- 
<number box="[1144,1175,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="20.0">20</number>
- 
<number box="[1183,1197,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="7.0">7</number>
.
</date>
R 
<number box="[1228,1236,347,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1245,1252,347,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="3.0">3</number>
and R 
<number box="[1323,1331,347,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1340,1347,347,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="5.0">5</number>
slightly concave; R 
<number box="[276,284,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[293,300,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[376,382,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[391,400,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="2.0">2</number>
rather divergent; M 
<number box="[623,629,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[639,648,386,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="2.0">2</number>
apex curved downward; r-m and dm-cu paralell, distant each other 
<number box="[1401,1436,370,394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="2.8">2.8</number>
as long as dm-cu. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,477,409,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[493,579,409,433]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[167,1409,883,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,845,1691]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 22. Habitus. 23. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 24. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214706/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[547,579,409,433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites dark brown, segment 
<number box="[1096,1110,409,433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="5.0">5</number>
lighter. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1334,409,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Hypandrium wide basally (
<figureCitation box="[391,478,445,469]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[167,1409,883,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,845,1691]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 22. Habitus. 23. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 24. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214706/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[447,478,445,469]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium without ventral projections; surstylus slender, with some bristles, not fused to epandrium; mesolobus bilobed (
<figureCitation box="[608,692,481,505]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[167,1409,883,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,845,1691]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 22. Habitus. 23. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 24. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214706/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[660,692,481,505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,649]" box="[199,418,517,542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,518,542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,649]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,553,578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Comments.</emphasis>
This is by far the darkest species known in the genus. The blackish markings in the pleural sclerites are shared with 
<taxonomicName box="[381,542,590,614]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Psilochlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paganelliae">
<emphasis box="[381,542,590,614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">P. paganelliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this latter species is much lighter and there are obvious differences in the male terminalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
